Type: Package
Package: ggtwotone
Title: Dual-Tone and Contrast-Aware ggplot2 Geoms
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Beenu", "Sareena", email = "beenusareena810@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Heike", "Hofmann", email = "hhofmann4@unl.edu", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Provides dual-stroke and contrast-aware extensions to
    'ggplot2', designed for improved visibility and accessibility in
    complex visualizations. Includes geoms for dual-stroke segments,
    regression lines, curved annotations, function plots, and adaptive
    text: 'geom_segment_dual()', 'geom_lm_dual()', 'geom_curve_dual()',
    'geom_curve_dual_function()', and 'geom_text_contrast()'. Also
    includes utility functions such as 'adjust_contrast_pair()',
    'geom_path_dual()', and 'highlight_colors()' for computing
    perceptually distinct color pairs and highlight palettes using WCAG-
    based contrast logic.
